Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.95,0:10:24.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the man that just\Nwent in hasn't 'come out yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.16,0:10:27.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll go check inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.86,0:10:30.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.04,0:10:38.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.88,0:10:51.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He seem to be looking for something...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.79,0:10:55.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Too bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.85,0:10:59.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not there, . no matter\Nhow hard you look.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.52,0:11:03.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a video tape that\Nis proof of our relationship.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.33,0:11:06.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,SO of course I hid it some place\Nvery special in this house!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.67,0:11:10.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm keeping it as a guarantee\Nthat-you will divorce
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.60,0:11:12.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,your wife and marry me instead. Sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.74,0:11:15.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My husband will be coming home soc
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.97,0:11:19.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,ou re 90mg < run mg WI 1 your\Ncollege friends, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.45,0:11:23.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You may relax on the sofa till then.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.82,0:11:36.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really, I don't understand\Nadults, honestly
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.40,0:11:39.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's scary 'cuz even your relationship\Nwith your wife who you've been living
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.43,0:11:41.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,separately from all these\Nyears seem to look better...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.40,0:11:42.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Be quite.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.50,0:11:43.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.64,0:11:46.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that guy from before?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.41,0:11:50.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder what he's doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.98,0:11:59.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's probably working overtime\Nbecause he can't fill his quota
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.05,0:12:03.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems her husband's\Nfinally come home
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.16,0:12:07.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ikm:home:
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.59,0:12:10.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh my. hello dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.20,0:12:12.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hello, Morosumi
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.70,0:12:15.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Soga. you're here already
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.03,0:12:15.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.83,0:12:18.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let me use the bathroom
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.00,0:12:21.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can you get the engine\Nrunning while you're waiting?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.61,0:12:24.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No! If you're going out drinking. walk!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.91,0:12:29.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay. And, would you like to\Ncome along too, for a{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}ge.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.31,0:12:31.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No thank you, because I can't drink
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.75,0:12:35.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I also want to watch the soccer\Ngame that will be aired at midnight,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.12,0:12:36.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,SHl'd like to take a short nap too...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.09,0:12:39.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Too bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.09,0:12:46.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The conversationthat the two men would\Nhave over drinks drew some interest but
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.13,0:12:48.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How long do you intend to\Nstay fooling around out there!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.95,0:12:50.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hurry up and come on home!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.20,0:12:55.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We got a call from Ran, so\Nwe decided to head on home...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.27,0:12:59.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Heiji! Just what do\Nyou think you're doing!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.81,0:13:03.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I went out of my way 1 make dinner\Nfor you and it's all cold already!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.05,0:13:05.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where are you now
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.88,0:13:08.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Morosumi residence where I\Naccepted the work of the detective...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.02,0:13:14.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? You just said you're headed\Nhome because you finished the job!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.59,0:13:14.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? You just said you're headed\Nhome because you finished the job!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.99,0:13:17.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's what we were planning to do,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.70,0:13:20.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but we passed a fire\Nengine on the way back.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.80,0:13:22.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We got concerned and\Nheaded back to the residence
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.80,0:13:24.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and found it blazing outrageously...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.00,0:13:28.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Morosumi residence...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.45,0:13:39.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's this way, hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.79,0:13:48.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,RRyoko...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.36,0:13:53.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems like that woman\Ndidn't escape in time...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.50,0:13:58.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we just kept watching,\Nthis wouldn't have happened...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.80,0:14:00.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But. isn't it strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.81,0:14:03.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those two went outsto drink-right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.01,0:14:07.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not even-an-hour has past yet. and I\Nwonder-why they:came back?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.15,0:14:09.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,True
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.78,0:14:12.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe they had a premonition\Nof some kind?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.52,0:14:15.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See, mommy, it came\Nafter all, didn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.79,0:14:18.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A red horse that causes fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.83,0:14:23.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey kid! How come you knew\Nthat a red horse was coming?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.83,0:14:25.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because I saw it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.40,0:14:27.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When and where?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.50,0:14:29.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey. who are you people?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.77,0:14:31.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You really saw it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.14,0:14:35.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm not lying! It was only\Nthe shadow of the horse, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.16,0:14:36.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shadow?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.04,0:14:36.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yep!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.88,0:14:41.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was when I was watching\NKamen Yaiba in the living room!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.35,0:14:44.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When Yaiba's first song started,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.38,0:14:46.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it suddenly got bright outside
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.35,0:14:49.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so I looked outside\Nand was surprised!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.22,0:14:53.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A shadow of a horse\Nabout this big was on the curtain!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.53,0:14:55.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which way I's your house?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.93,0:14:59.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the right of the burning house?\NOr, on the left?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.26,0:15:00.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To the right!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.34,0:15:04.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H Hey?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.66,0:15:14.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A horse, by the window!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.25,0:15:15.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a red horse!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.97,0:15:21.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means that the room ta boy\Nwas watching TV in, is this room
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.39,0:15:25.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, the shadow, of the horse\Nshowed up on this curtain...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.16,0:15:29.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kaimen Yaiba starts at 7:30 pm
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.90,0:15:34.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it got bright during the opening of the\Nprogram and the shadow was reflected
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.08,0:15:39.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The arsonist set fire and put-the\Nhorse in place a little after 7:30 pm
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.80,0:15:45.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, at least we know that the arsonist\Nwas near this window about that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.78,0:15:52.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uh, so the horse set the\Nfire after all, right, mommy?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.59,0:16:02.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Two hours later, the fire that took the life of\N"oko Moresumi W's finally extinguished
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.80,0:16:08.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Will you let me in just for a minute?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.23,0:16:09.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.94,0:16:12.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, will you at least tell me\Nwhere the fire first broke out?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.47,0:16:14.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.11,0:16:17.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's the big deal\Ngiving out a little info?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.04,0:16:20.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't do what I can't do,\Neven if it's for you, Mr. Mouiril!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.08,0:16:25.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, the scene of a fire is not territory\Nfor the homicide division, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.95,0:16:28.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,0.0ld man fire of the 1st division?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.72,0:16:33.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Mouri! How dare you call\Nyour former superior old man fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.49,0:16:35.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Former superior?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.33,0:16:37.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Yuminaga of the Metropolitan
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.76,0:16:40.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Police Arson Investigation\NDivision section 1!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.93,0:16:43.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought you belonged to\Nthe homicide division?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.94,0:16:46.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I used to be in the arson\Ndivision for a little while...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.67,0:16:51.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You sure caused me a lot of agony.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.08,0:16:55.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Every time there's a fire you claim that it's\Narson and go out to the scene of the fire,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.68,0:16:57.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and step all over the\Npersonal effects left there...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.68,0:17:00.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,God knows how many complaints\NI got of you from the fire department
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.42,0:17:01.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.95,0:17:04.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The same goes for you too
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.46,0:17:07.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This fire is undoubtedly arson
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.29,0:17:11.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The red horse was found\Nat the site of this fire too
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.16,0:17:15.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We checked it out\Nwith the forensic officers and
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.07,0:17:16.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,found that it was a perfect match\Nwith the other three horses.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.07,0:17:19.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Mr. Yuminaga,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.04,0:17:21.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,isn't there a possibility that\Nsomebody who saw the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.91,0:17:24.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the incident in the newspaper or\Nsomething tried copying?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.88,0:17:25.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You foo!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.31,0:17:30.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How can you make the exact same\Nhorse by just seeing it in the papers?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.12,0:17:34.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That plastic horse is made\Nof the same mold.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.79,0:17:36.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And is not sold anywhere
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.99,0:17:40.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so the arsonist probably\Ntook fun in making it himself
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.36,0:17:44.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The arsonist was probably having\Nfun challenging the police,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.36,0:17:46.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but somebody has been killed this time...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.90,0:17:49.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, the fun's over...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.50,0:17:51.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, where did the fire start?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.80,0:17:55.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who's this boy here, your assistant?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.97,0:17:57.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y.Yes, well, sort of...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.83,0:18:02.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The fire started in the hut\Nbeyond the right side of the house
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.68,0:18:05.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The storeroom with the window\Nwhere the red horse was placed
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.42,0:18:09.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There were traces of\Nkerosene poured on the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.39,0:18:11.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, the arsonist probably\Npoured the kerosene
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.51,0:18:14.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,in from the open window and set fire
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.69,0:18:19.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There were a lot of strange footprints by
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.86,0:18:22.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the window of the room in the\Nforeground of the storeroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.03,0:18:25.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we check the footprints carefully
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.04,0:18:27.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure we'll at least get to\Ngrab the tail of the arsonist
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.54,0:18:31.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, well, the thing is...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.24,0:18:33.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.78,0:18:37.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your footprints are mixed up\Nin the footprints there?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.62,0:18:42.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm actually here because I was asked\Nto come here by Mrs. Ryoko Morosumi,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.85,0:18:45.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the victim who died of the fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.17,0:18:48.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She asked me to come\Ncheck on a suspicious person
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.59,0:18:51.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,who was doing something\Naround her house late at night...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.60,0:18:55.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the lady said that it was\Njust her imagination and told
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.37,0:18:58.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,us to leave, so we were\Nwatching her for a while...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.50,0:19:03.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then a strange character who seemed to\Nbe a Feng Shui Sensei came by,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.17,0:19:04.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so having no other choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.48,0:19:07.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We went into her yard and looked inside
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.63,0:19:09.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,through the window\Nand saw a pretty bad scene
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.65,0:19:11.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Pretty bad scene?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.62,0:19:14.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems that this man:was having\Nan extra-marital affair with Ryoko,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.95,0:19:17.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and was ransacking the rooms looking
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.52,0:19:19.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,for the video that\Nwas evidence of their affair!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.89,0:19:24.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That act of yours sounds more\Nthan pretty bad to me...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.30,0:19:29.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, but I guess I'll have to\Ntake molds of your shoes later!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.10,0:19:32.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me you think\Nthat we're suspects?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.37,0:19:37.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You fool! It's to discriminate your\Nfootprints with the arsonist's!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.78,0:19:44.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that man that had an affair with her,\Nthe only one that came by the house?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.75,0:19:47.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,N.No, four people came in all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.82,0:19:51.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That man who had the affair\Nand Ryoko's husband
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.56,0:19:54.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ryoko's older sister who\Nseems to be a fortuneteller.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.59,0:19:58.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A timid guy who came and left\Ncatalog of his store with her...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.66,0:20:04.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, the Sensei of Feng Shui and\NRyoko's husband are not arsonists.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.30,0:20:07.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,According to the testimony\Nof the kid next door,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.54,0:20:11.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the red horse was placed\Nby the window at exactly 7:30 pm!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.48,0:20:15.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Sensei and her husband went\Nout to drink at about 7:20 pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.88,0:20:17.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,SO the two couldn't have done it...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.22,0:20:23.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And we were contemplating for about 5\Nminutes whether to follow the two or not,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.19,0:20:25.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but at that time there\Nwas No smoke nor fire at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.62,0:20:30.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only concern is why those two came\Nback so early despite having gone drinking
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.23,0:20:35.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that's because a neighbor\Ncalled the husband's
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.47,0:20:38.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,cell phone and told him there! as a fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.04,0:20:44.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which leaves the older sister who is a\Nfortuneteller and the timid man...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.84,0:20:47.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Talking of fortunetelling,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.85,0:20:54.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, the lady may be there!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.59,0:20:56.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.52,0:21:01.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What! Ryoko died?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.19,0:21:02.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you serious?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.76,0:21:03.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.56,0:21:06.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What a foolish child.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.43,0:21:10.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I warned her time and\Nagain to be careful because
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.97,0:21:13.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I saw signs of disaster by fire in her!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.51,0:21:15.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Our father's funeral is not finished yet,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.54,0:21:17.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,still why is everybody\Ncrossing over like this?
